OL,5, The number of adults struggling to pay 
OL,6, their bills and debts has soared to    
OL,7, nearly 11 million, new figures show.   
OL,9,FSome 3.1 million more people faced     
OL,10,Fdifficulties in January than they did  
OL,11,Fin May last year, the Financial Conduct
OL,12,FAuthority (FCA) said.                  
OL,14,FIt found that 11% of adults had missed 
OL,15,Fa bill or loan payment in at least     
OL,16,Fthree of the previous six months.      
OL,18,FThe FCA encouraged people to ask for   
OL,19,Fhelp as household budgets were squeezed
OL,20,Fby the rising cost of living.          
